SELF-LEARNING UPDATE — Bookforge final-chapter external review repair workflow

Add this to the Bookforge Lab learning ledger / model-scorecard operating layer.

Future final-chapter external review repairs should follow this safe pattern:
- back up promoted chapters and state first;
- tighten surgically, not broad rewrite, when the chapter is usable but overlong;
- remove repeated slogans/catchphrases across promoted chapters, not only the final chapter;
- preserve evidence/custody/open-ending logic unless the review proves a real contradiction;
- compress over-explained prop origins;
- rename late minor-character name collisions;
- add small injury/continuity reminders when an injury fades;
- reassemble manuscript offline from promoted chapter files;
- verify with no-token checks/searches;
- do not clear unrelated Bookforge quality holds;
- do not resume Bookforge generation without explicit approval.

The Last Safe Lie Chapter 14 example: external review asked for 15–20% tightening, DNR supervisor Aris rename, shorter cassette origin, repeated bait/hidden/real proof reduction, less culvert repetition, and removal of the repeated final-line slogan. Repair cut Chapter 14 about 18.8%, renamed Aris to Graham, compressed the cassette origin, removed the repeated final line from promoted Chapters 2, 3, 8, 10, 11, 13, and 14, reassembled the manuscript with 14 chapters/no missing chapters, left the separate quality_hold untouched, and did not resume spending.

Future prevention rule: review note -> verify in promoted text -> backup -> surgical edit -> whole-book repeated phrase search -> reassemble -> local no-token checks -> leave unrelated holds untouched -> Steward approval before any resume.
